article.headline: Fordham 45, Marist 21
article.story: NEW YORK -- John Skelton threw four touchdown passes to help the Rams beat Marist 45-21 Saturday. Skelton, whose longest scoring pass was a 38-yarder to Bo Marchand, finished 22-of-28 for 341. The Rams (4-4) led 38-7 at the half, after Adam Danko's 24-yard field goal as time expired in the 1st half. Xavier Martin ran for touchdowns of 10 and 5 yards and finished with 122 yards on 27 carries. The Rams led 21-0 before Bo Ehikioya put the Red Foxes (3-6) on the board with a 17-yard run midway through the second quarter.
